CPC leader Certain About Economic Growth Target
BEIJING , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- Wei Jianxing , a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China ( CPC ) , told a Cuban trade union delegation here today that China can reach its eight-percent economic growth target and keep its currency stable .
Wei was meeting with Pedro Ross , a member of the Political Bureau of the Cuban Communist Party Central Committee and secretary-general of the Federation of Cuban Workers , who headed the delegation .
Wei said that , although Asian financial crisis has had some negative effects on the economy , the Government is increasing infrastructure spending and domestic markets to boost economic growth .
Wei discussed the 15th CPC National Congress and the 13th National Congress of trade unions and said that Chinese trade unions are ready to increase exchanges and cooperation with their Cuban counterparts .
Ross spoke highly of China 's achievements since it adopted its reforms and opening up to the outside world and discussed Cuba 's reforms and development of its economy under the leadership of the Cuban Communist Party .
